1.title: I Gotta Have Two Legs to Run the Race!
1.plot: Australia v New Zealand. Ten teams comprising of two people from either Australia or New Zealand compete in this race around the world. The first team to finish receives A$250,000. Representing Australia are dating bodybuilders Sally and Tyson, intensive care nurses Daniel and Ryan, mother and son Elizabeth and Todd, pageant models Inga and Tiharna and newlyweds Ashleigh and Jarrod, and representing New Zealand are siblings Emily and Jono, fitness mothers Carla and Hereni, foster parents Cat and Jesse, best mates John and Murray and feisty friends Aston and Christie.

1.title: Nothing's Smooth Sailing with Us (Indonesia)
1.plot: Eleven teams of two people travel from Melbourne, Victoria to Lombok, Indonesia. Some people have to battle both the wind and a fear of heights at the Road Block.

2.title: Like Four Seasons in a Day (Vietnam)
2.plot: The eleven teams travel from Lombok, Indonesia to Hue, Vietnam. Many teams struggle to find flights out of Indonesia. One team asks about getting off the island by bus, while another team cannot agree on how they should get to Vietnam, causing sparks to fly.

3.title: We've Got Pain, But We've Not Lost Any Weight (Hong Kong and Macau, China)
3.plot: The ten remaining teams travel from Hue, Vietnam to Macau, China. They all have to search for a good fortune among hundreds of cookies in Hong Kong, but will any of them be brave enough to attempt a hair-raising Fast Forward?

4.title: A Town That Was 15-20 Letters Long (Port Elizabeth, South Africa)
4.plot: The nine remaining teams travel from Macau, China to Waterford, South Africa, where they have to scale great heights to face their greatest fears. One team embraces the African traditions, while another team falls foul of the law.

5.title: The Woman-ness to Realize Where You Went Wrong (Cape Town, South Africa)
5.plot: The eight remaining teams stay in South Africa as they travel from Waterford to Cape Town. A visit to a local orphanage to deliver some much needed school supplies helps to put the competition into perspective for some teams.

6.title: The Last Team Will Spend the Night in the Dungeon (Netherlands and Czech Republic)
6.plot: The seven remaining teams travel from Cape Town, South Africa to Prague, Czech Republic. In Amsterdam, the teams are challenged to stomach a local delicacy. At Prague, the friendships start to splinter, and one team's decision to put the prize ahead of maintaining the relationships they have built up could come back to haunt them. At the Detour, some teams struggle to find the key to a damsel's heart, while others have their strength put to the test when they deliver a princess to her castle.

7.title: It's Just Like Where's Wally (Prague, Czech Republic)
7.plot: The six remaining teams stay in the Czech Republic as they travel from Prague to Kutná Hora. Not all of the teams are as observant as they need to be when they become Czech spies. Some teams find a visit to the ice skating rink to line up against the national ice hockey team's goalkeeper to be the most physically gruelling challenge so far. One team find themselves in trouble with the law twice, while a local sausage sizzle doesn't appeal to everyone's taste buds at the Detour.

8.title: At Least the View's Nice (Poland)
8.plot: The six teams continue the leg as they travel from Kutná Hora, Czech Republic to Niedzica, Poland, battling fatigue along the way. One team is robbed of their money and passports while they are on board a train for Poland. One person from each team heads underground in one of the world's oldest salt mines at the Road Block, while herding sheep frustrates some of the teams at the Detour. The final challenge ends in disaster for more than one team.

9.title: When I Saw Everyone Freezing to Death (Tel Aviv, Israel)
9.plot: The five remaining teams travel from Niedzica, Poland to Masada, Israel, where they face a daunting journey through the Middle Eastern heat to a desert fortress. One team fails to make it to the Pit Stop.

10.title: I Hope We Don't Have to Wear a Crown of Thorns (Jerusalem, Israel)
10.plot: The four remaining teams stay in Israel as they travel from Masada to Jerusalem. The teams' knowledge of Hebrew is put to the test at the Road Block. Scaling the walls of Jerusalem's old city proves to be a difficult final hurdle.

11.title: Sri Lanka
11.plot: The four teams travel from Jerusalem, Israel to Colombo, Sri Lanka. A decision about which class carriage to ride in during a train trip could prove costly for one team. They all struggle with their history, but a masked street parade gives them the opportunity to make up for lost time. A sewing challenge turns into a disaster for all of the teams at the Road Block.

12.title: You're Good at Spending Money (Singapore and Western Australia)
12.plot: The final three teams travel from Colombo, Sri Lanka to Perth, Western Australia. In Singapore, a tightrope walk 55 storeys high puts some of the teams' nerves to the test at the Detour, before they seek their riches from a local fortune teller. At their final destination city, they search some cells in Fremantle Prison for a clue before struggling to remember their journey's highlights at the Road Block. The first team to reach the finish line wins the A$250,000 prize.

1.title: Daraga, The Philippines
1.plot: Eleven new teams of 2 travel from Sydney, New South Wales to Cagraray, Philippines, on the first leg of a race that promises to be longer and more challenging than ever. The first team to finish receives a prize never offered before in the race's history.

2.title: New Delhi, India
2.plot: The eleven teams travel from Cagraray, Philippines to Delhi, India. Sparks fly when one team struggle to navigate Delhi's chaotic streets. A breach of the race rules could prove costly for one team.

3.title: Jaipur, India
3.plot: The ten remaining teams stay in India when a bus takes them from Delhi to Jaipur during the rest period. On their arrival, they have to undertake a driving test on the exotic city's chaotic streets. A run-in between two teams sends one of them reeling.

4.title: Dubai, United Arab Emirates
4.plot: The nine remaining teams travel from Jaipur, India to Dubai, United Arab Emirates. Finding transport to get them through Dubai's stunning deserts from A to B may prove to be the biggest challenge of all at the Detour. A wrong turn leads to one team finding themselves in serious trouble when they are arrested. Will they be the team that fails to make it to the Pit Stop?

5.title: Istanbul, Turkey Part 1
5.plot: The eight remaining teams travel from Dubai, United Arab Emirates to Istanbul, Turkey. Some teams turn on workmates Paul & Steve while other teams turn on themselves. A market challenge that appears to be simple will put every team's patience to the test at the Detour.

6.title: Istanbul, Turkey Part 2
6.plot: The eight teams stay in Istanbul, Turkey, where among the challenges they face are soapy baths, oil wrestling and shoe shining. Will some teams be pushed to breaking point by the pressure as the competition heats up?

7.title: Havana, Cuba Part 1
7.plot: The seven remaining teams travel from Istanbul, Turkey to Havana, Cuba. Teams get excited when they learn that they have to fly to Paris, France, but there is a lot of hatred in the City of Love when one team steals another team's taxi. The biggest leg yet will test the teams like never before.

8.title: Havana, Cuba Part 2
8.plot: The seven teams continue the leg in Cuba as they travel from Havana to Guamá. The team who stole a taxi from another team in the previous leg find the consequences to be far-reaching. A Detour involving two Cuban icons ends with shattering results for one team. The teams receive a surprise when they learn that they must drive to Australia.

9.title: Vancouver
9.plot: The six remaining teams are transported from Guamá, Cuba back to Havana during the rest period, from where they travel to Vancouver, Canada. A sleep-in could prove costly for one team. One of the race's biggest and most spectacular challenges puts some teams' limits to the test at the Road Block. One team crumbles under the pressure at the Detour.

10.title: Banff
10.plot: The five remaining teams stay in Canada as they travel from Vancouver to Banff. Climbing a frozen waterfall at the Road Block proves to be particularly tough for one of the favourite teams. Tempers flare when the teams hit the ski slopes.

11.title: Beijing
11.plot: The four remaining teams travel from Banff, Canada to Beijing, China. As they battle for a place in the final three who will race to the finish, they are in for a shock when they receive a "massage". One team makes a costly mistake on the way to the Great Wall.

12.title: Finale
12.plot: The final three teams are transported from Beijing, China to Guilin during the rest period, from where they travel to Fraser Island, Queensland. A few extra seconds spent at the airport helps one team to gain what could be a race-winning edge later. The first team to reach the finish line wins the A$250,000 first prize.
